This paper is about a language representation model that incorporates domain-specific knowledge using knowledge graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses information retrieval and database-related concepts, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
